																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>The <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/275023773_The_Push_-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">traditional push-up</a> movement has been around for thousands of years. Indian warriors were said to have used it to improve their strength level and stay in shape.&nbsp; Even the Roman emperor Constantine was rumored to have done push-ups to stay in shape during his reign.</p>



<p>However, it wasn’t until the early 1900s that the push-up would become well-recognized throughout society. Since then, several <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/push-up-variations" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">push up variations</a> have been widely adopted. These are commonly used to change the difficulty or target certain muscle groups.</p>



<p>The Hindu push up, or dand push-up in India, is an advanced push-up variation that uses a dynamic movement. It requires no equipment, works multiple muscle groups, and improves general fitness.</p>



<p>With its current popularity, we’ve detailed some of the amazing benefits you can expect when performing it. We also detail the correct form and tips on how to master this versatile bodyweight movement.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">Why You Should Put Hindu Push Up Into Your Routine</p>



<p>The Hindu push up is a challenging variation that combines the normal push-up with an overhead press and back extension. This makes it a dynamic hybrid movement that requires additional strength and core stability.</p>



<p>These are the main benefits of Hindu push ups:</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Improves-Posture-and-Flexibility">Improves posture and flexibility.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Increases-Functional-Strength">Increases functional strength.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Strengthens-Multiple-Muscle-Groups">Strengthens multiple muscle groups.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Enhances-muscular-endurance.">Enhances muscular endurance.</a></li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">4 Top Benefits of Hindu Push-Ups</h2>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/training/benefits-of-push-ups" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">benefits of push-ups</a> are well documented. These are four benefits of Hindu push-ups that make them worthwhile to perform.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Improves-Posture-and-Flexibility">Improves Posture &amp; Flexibility</h3>



<p>Poor <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5869197/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">posture</a> and flexibility are prevalent issues throughout today&#8217;s society. A study found that <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC9556879/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">70.5%</a> of university respondents complained of muscular discomfort after prolonged work at home.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Seated work and transport positions <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/13/19/10935" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">promote poor posture</a> over long periods. This includes rounding the shoulders and slouching. When this happens, it places unnecessary stress on the lower back region.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Hindu push-ups strengthen your shoulders, back, and core. The scapula (shoulder blade) muscles work to maintain the correct arm positions during both movement phases. The glutes and hamstrings stretch as you come back to the starting position.</p>



<p>Each of these helps to maintain an upright posture. When seated, they keep the chest up and head looking forward. During movement, they contribute to limb stability and ensure efficient movement patterns.&nbsp;</p>



<p>A <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/369894336_Effect_of_scapular_strengthening_exercises_on_rounded_shoulder_and_neck_disability_among_college_students_of_Delhi_NCR#:~:text=Results%20demonstrated%20that%20the%20experimental,disability%20and%20rounded%20shoulder%20posture." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">study</a> looking at the effect of scapula strengthening exercise on rounded shoulder posture found improvements after four weeks. Simple exercises were used involving shoulder extension and bringing the scapula inwards or outwards from the spine.</p>



<p>With this, we can say that the Hindu push-up works many of the key postural and flexibility muscles. Over a prolonged period, performing them may help improve posture and flexibility.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Increases-Functional-Strength">Increases Functional Strength</h3>



<p>Functional strength is the ability of the body to perform movement and activity commonly done in daily life. Functional strength training aims to improve this by mimicking these functional movements. When done correctly, everyday tasks may become <a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-jscr/fulltext/2019/06000/effects_of_functional_strength_training_program_on.10.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">easier with less injury risk</a>.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The Hindu push-up uses the chest, shoulders, and triceps as primary movers. These muscle groups are <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10889156/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">heavily involved</a> in many functional pressing motions. This includes things such as throwing a ball or putting a heavy object away overhead.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The core musculature is much more involved compared to a normal push-up during this exercise. The added core challenge helps to improve core stability, a vital component of <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/322973201_The_Effect_of_Core_Stability_Training_on_Functional_Movement_Patterns_in_Collegiate_Athletes" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">functional strength</a>. Because of this, the Hindu push-up is a great bodyweight exercise to improve functional strength.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Strengthens-Multiple-Muscle-Groups">Strengthens Multiple Muscle Groups</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/hindu-push-up-benefits-1.jpg" alt="hindu push up train multiple muscle groups" class="wp-image-27278" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/hindu-push-up-benefits-1.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/hindu-push-up-benefits-1-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/hindu-push-up-benefits-1-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/hindu-push-up-benefits-1-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/hindu-push-up-benefits-1-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Hindu Push Up help train multiple muscle groups. <span>Photo: ibrakovic/Freepik</span></figcaption></figure>



<p>Compound exercises require multiple muscle groups to work together to perform them correctly. They’re also known as multi-joint movements. These are proven to be <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5744434/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">better for muscular strength</a> and oxygen consumption when compared to single-joint movements.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The Hindu push-up is an advanced variation that uses a dynamic movement pattern. Because of this, it requires several muscle groups to work together.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The clavicular head of the pectoralis major and anterior deltoids (front deltoids) flex the arms. This means they bring them in front and above the body. This happens as you assume the inverted V-shape and push out of the bottom position.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The sternal heads of the pectoralis major adduct the arms, bringing them into the midline of the body. This also happens when you push from the bottom position. The abdominal heads of the pectoralis major extend the arms behind the body as you lower down to the floor.</p>



<p>The triceps brachii <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5827912/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">extend the elbows</a> in both phases of the movement. The core musculature maintains a stable body position while the glutes and hamstrings stretch as you adopt the inverted V-shape.</p>



<p>This makes it a challenging bodyweight exercise that works multiple muscle groups. When performed correctly with the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4562558/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">right intensity</a>, this can provide a full-body strength exercise.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Enhances-muscular-endurance.">Enhances Muscular Endurance</h3>



<p><a href="https://journals.lww.com/acsm-healthfitness/fulltext/2016/09000/shareable_resource__muscular_strength_versus.3.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Muscular endurance</a> refers to how long a muscle can sustain a certain exercise stimulus. Enhancing this may help to improve overall health and fitness, maintain posture, carry out functional activity, and improve performance.</p>



<p>The Hindu push-up requires the upper body, core musculature, and lower body muscles to maintain the correct movement pattern. These muscle groups perform repeated muscle contractions over a sustained period during each set. This provides a great way to improve muscular endurance using a bodyweight movement pattern.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Alongside this, the Hindu push-up requires no equipment to perform or no cost. Because of this, it has <a href="https://bmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12889-022-13431-2" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">no barrier to access</a>.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This makes it easier to perform it whenever needed to improve training volume. This refers to the amount of work performed. More training volume can <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6303131/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">improve muscular endurance</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What Is A Hindu Push-Up?</h2>



<p>A popular and possibly older variation currently gaining traction throughout fitness communities is the <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/hindu-push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Hindu push-up</a>. Its origins can be traced back to ancient India, centuries before any equipment was invented. Hindu warriors and yogis are said to have used it to build strength and physical stature.</p>



<p>The specific history of the Hindu push-up is still widely debated throughout exercise circles. Some people suggest it was done by Hindu warriors to prepare for battle. Others believe it was developed by yogis who wanted to improve their flexibility and balance.</p>



<p>Whoever invented it, it&#8217;s clear that the Hindu push-up has been rooted in Indian culture for centuries. Some historians believe it was first mentioned in ancient texts such as the Mahabharata and Bhagavad Gita. This would date it back to the fifth century BC, making us wonder just how far push-up history goes back.</p>



<p>Hindu push-ups are a challenging variation that combines the normal <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">push-up</a> movement with an overhead press and back extension. They’re performed using one fluid movement pattern, making them a dynamic and challenging bodyweight movement.&nbsp;</p>



<p>They require muscular strength, core stability, and full-body coordination. This may provide several <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10588579/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">performance applications</a> and reduce injury risk. Here’s how to do them.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-end">How To Do Hindu Pushups?</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Hindu Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1008435692?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Hindu Push Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h3>



<ol>
<li>Find a suitable padded area or gym mat and assume a tabletop position. Your knees should be on the ground with your hands on the floor, shoulder-width apart.</li>
</ol>



<ol start="2">
<li>Extend both legs back and come onto the balls of your feet to assume a high plank position. Slowly walk your hands back to form an inverted V-shape. Your hips should be facing directly up towards the ceiling.</li>
</ol>



<ol start="3">
<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and flex (bend) both elbows, lowering your body down at a 45-degree angle. Allow your head to come down at a 45-degree angle while your shoulders extend back.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<ol start="4">
<li>As your arms come behind your body, bring your head past your hands. Extend your spine and allow your upper body to come off the floor. Extend your elbows once your head passes your arms.</li>
</ol>



<ol start="5">
<li>Pause briefly at the bottom position. Inhale and flex your shoulders, allowing your head to come back through your arms. Extend your elbows to press back up to the starting position.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Tips To Master</h3>



<ul>
<li><strong>Engage Your Core — </strong>Keep your core engaged throughout the movement pattern. This helps to provide a stable body position as you go through the movements. Avoid letting your back round or hips come down.</li>



<li><strong>Control The Movement —</strong> The dynamic movements require balance to keep the focus on the targeted exercise. Perform both phases using the same <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/351905034_The_Influence_of_Movement_Tempo_During_Resistance_Training_on_Muscular_Strength_and_Hypertrophy_Responses_A_Review">movement tempo</a> to maintain balance and exercise focus.</li>



<li><strong>Assume The Correct Position —</strong> Stay on your hands and the balls of your feet throughout the movement. This is the correct exercise position that helps to prevent joint stress.</li>



<li><strong>Keep A Neutral Neck And Head — </strong>Ensure that your head follows the movement of your body. This helps to limit potential neck strain and injury.&nbsp;</li>



<li><strong>Maintain A Shoulder-Width Arm Position — </strong>Your arms should be shoulder-width apart with your hands pointing slightly out. This provides targeted muscle activation and limits potential wrist stress.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Conclusion</h2>



<p>Whether it’s a yoga-inspired push-up or a Hindu warrior staple, Hindu push-ups are a versatile movement with several benefits. They can be performed anywhere as part of a functional exercise routine or a high-quality conditioning workout.</p>



<p>While the exact history of the Hindu push-up is still up for debate, the benefits are clear. Add it to your workout routine and start to see the rewards.</p>



